      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a benchmark of analog performance. Under the hood lies the S54 3.2L straight-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and double VANOS, delivering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. This example features the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. The chassis has been maintained with an eye toward longevity, including documented subframe reinforcement and a recent valve adjustment. While it exhibits the expected patina of a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the powertrain remains tight with excellent compression. It is a turn-key enthusiast machine ready for the canyon or the track.",
